column1: The coverage with a star correspond to coverage retrieved from the NCBI genome metadata as no reads were available at the time of our study. BUSCOs statistics are from a BUSCOv3 search on the hymenoptera odb9 dataset. Other genomic statistics have been calculated using the soft quast.

Since all ants and bees are known to have free-living lifestyles since their common ancestor, references for the lifestyle of all species from the Formicoidea and Apoidea superfamily all come from the same generalistic bilibographies.
